1
00:00:03,570 --> 00:00:05,971
<i> [ Man ]</i>
<i> JAROD BOOKED OUT OF HERE</i>
<i> A COUPLE DAYS AGO.</i>

2
00:00:06,040 --> 00:00:07,973
I SURE MISS THAT OLD BOY.

3
00:00:08,041 --> 00:00:10,976
TO KNOW HIM IS TO LOVE HIM.
AMEN, BROTHER.

4
00:00:11,045 --> 00:00:15,047
I KIND OF TOOK HIM
UNDER MY WING, SO TO SPEAK.
YEAH, I KEPT MY EYE ON HIM.

5
00:00:15,115 --> 00:00:17,749
I'M SURE THAT'S
JUST LIKE YOU, JUNIOR, ALWAYS
THINKING OF THE OTHER GUY.

6
00:00:17,818 --> 00:00:21,286
I BELIEVE IN HELPIN' THOSE
LESS FORTUNATE.

7
00:00:23,290 --> 00:00:26,024
"DARWIN TRANSPORT."
YEP, THIS IS IT.

8
00:00:26,092 --> 00:00:28,560
- THIS IS WHAT?
JAROD STAYED IN THAT?
-<i> YEP.</i>

9
00:00:28,629 --> 00:00:31,163
HE'D LOCK HIMSELF IN THERE
FOR THREE, FOUR DAYS AT A TIME.

10
00:00:31,232 --> 00:00:33,365
PAID ME TO CHECK IN ON HIM
NOW AND AGAIN.

11
00:00:33,434 --> 00:00:36,668
<i>YOU KNOW,</i>
<i>BRING HIM A LITTLE BREAD,</i>
<i>SOME WATER, CHAIN HIM UP--</i>

12
00:00:36,736 --> 00:00:38,670
[ Together ]
CHAIN HIM UP?
LIVE AND LET LIVE.

13
00:00:38,739 --> 00:00:42,207
THAT'S MY MOTTO, ESPECIALLY WHEN
THERE'S CASH COMIN' MY WAY.

14
00:00:42,276 --> 00:00:46,211
<i>HELL, HE'D EVEN ASK ME</i>
<i>TO ZAP HIM WITH A CAR BATTERY</i>
<i>NOW AND THEN.</i>

15
00:00:46,280 --> 00:00:49,147
WHATEVER TURNS YOU ON,
I GUESS.

16
00:00:49,216 --> 00:00:51,350
- WHY, JAROD!
- JAROD!

17
00:00:51,418 --> 00:00:54,519
I DIDN'T KNOW YOU WAS IN THERE!

18
00:00:54,588 --> 00:00:56,855
<i> I GOT YA, DIDN'T I?</i>
<i> [ Wheezy Laugh ]</i>

19
00:00:59,159 --> 00:01:02,694
BUY YOURSELF
A FIFTH OF HAPPINESS.

20
00:01:02,763 --> 00:01:06,765
<i> I COULDN'T GET</i>
<i> A SHOT OF JOY FOR THIS.</i>

21
00:01:17,845 --> 00:01:20,611
THERE'S NO PLACE LIKE HOME.

22
00:01:20,680 --> 00:01:24,883
WELL, THEY SAY
THERE'S A FINE LINE
BETWEEN GENIUS AND INSANITY.

23
00:01:24,952 --> 00:01:27,285
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>
<i>JAROD'S LINE WAS ERASED</i>
<i>LONG AGO.</i>

24
00:01:28,489 --> 00:01:31,723
HUH. WHAT'S A HOME
WITHOUT TV?

25
00:01:36,763 --> 00:01:40,599
THAT'S JAROD'S HANDWRITING.
SINCE WHEN DO WE FOLLOW
HIS DIRECTIONS?

26
00:01:40,668 --> 00:01:42,601
THERE'S ALWAYS A METHOD
TO JAROD'S MADNESS.

27
00:01:42,670 --> 00:01:47,606
SO IF IT SAYS DON'T TOUCH,
DON'T TOUCH.

28
00:01:54,782 --> 00:01:57,482
<i>[ Buzzer Sounds ]</i>
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>
<i> LYLE!</i>

29
00:01:57,551 --> 00:02:00,885
OH, NO.

30
00:02:00,954 --> 00:02:03,955
<i> IT WON'T BUDGE.</i>
<i> JUNIOR? JUNIOR!</i>

31
00:02:04,024 --> 00:02:06,925
<i>[ Junior ]</i>
<i>SEE YOU LATER,</i>
<i>MISS PARKER, MR. LYLE!</i>

32
00:02:06,993 --> 00:02:09,594
OH, DAMN IT!

33
00:02:09,663 --> 00:02:12,731
WE NEVER TOLD THAT
SCUM-TOOTHED IDIOT OUR NAMES!

34
00:02:15,002 --> 00:02:17,736
JAROD SET THIS UP.

35
00:02:17,804 --> 00:02:19,771
NOW WE'RE HIS PRISONERS.

36
00:02:21,342 --> 00:02:24,676
<i>[ Helicopter Passing Overhead ]</i>

37
00:02:24,745 --> 00:02:26,678
WORST HEAT WAVE
WE'VE HAD IN YEARS,

38
00:02:26,747 --> 00:02:29,414
AND THIS ONE'S BEEN LOCKED
IN THE HOLE FOR THREE DAYS.

39
00:02:31,752 --> 00:02:35,487
<i>WE'RE GONNA NEED TO</i>
<i>SCRAPE HIM OUT WITH A SHOVEL.</i>

40
00:02:35,555 --> 00:02:37,522
[ Jarod ]
THANKS, BUT THAT
WON'T BE NECESSARY.

41
00:02:40,093 --> 00:02:42,026
I COULD USE A SHOWER, THOUGH.

42
00:02:44,230 --> 00:02:47,366
<i>[ Man Narrating ]</i>
<i>THERE ARE PRETENDERS AMONG US.</i>

43
00:02:47,434 --> 00:02:49,367
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>
<i>I WAS TAKEN FROM MY FAMILY.</i>

44
00:02:49,436 --> 00:02:53,004
<i>THIRTY-SIX HOURS AND HE'S</i>
<i>ALREADY DEMONSTRATING MORE</i>
<i>TALENT THAN ANY OF OUR OTHERS.</i>

45
00:02:53,073 --> 00:02:56,475
<i>HOW MANY PEOPLE DIED</i>
<i>BECAUSE OF WHAT I THOUGHT UP?</i>

46
00:02:56,543 --> 00:02:59,977
SINCE I BROKE OUT,
I'VE SPENT EVERY MOMENT
SEARCHING FOR MY PAST.

47
00:03:00,046 --> 00:03:02,246
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>
<i>HE'S A PRETENDER--</i>

48
00:03:02,315 --> 00:03:05,617
<i>A GENIUS WHO CAN BECOME</i>
<i>ANYONE THAT HE WANTS TO BE.</i>

49
00:03:05,685 --> 00:03:07,886
- THE CENTRE WANTS HIM ALIVE.
- PREFERABLY.

50
00:03:07,954 --> 00:03:10,121
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>
<i>HE DEFENDS THE WEAK AND ABUSED.</i>

51
00:03:10,190 --> 00:03:11,956
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>
<i>LIFE'S A GIFT.</i>

52
00:03:22,669 --> 00:03:25,203
-<i> YOU A DOCTOR?</i>
- I AM TODAY.

53
00:03:33,446 --> 00:03:36,248
<i> ♪♪ [ Jarod Whistling ]</i>

54
00:03:41,188 --> 00:03:43,722
GOOD MORNING, GENTLEMEN.

55
00:03:43,790 --> 00:03:47,926
[ Groans ]
EXCUSE ME, SIR.
IF YOU DON'T MIND MY SAYING,

56
00:03:47,994 --> 00:03:51,329
IT'S CREEPY THAT YOU JUST SPENT
THE LAST THREE DAYS IN THE SAME
HOLE OFFICER RION HUNG HIMSELF.

57
00:03:51,398 --> 00:03:53,331
SOMETIMES, YOU GOTTA WALK
IN SOMEBODY ELSE'S SHOES...

58
00:03:53,400 --> 00:03:55,400
TO UNDERSTAND
WHAT THEY'VE BEEN THROUGH.

59
00:03:55,469 --> 00:03:57,235
CALL IT A... SIMULATION.

60
00:03:57,304 --> 00:03:59,738
IS THAT SOMETHING
THEY TEACH YOU IN CRIMINAL
INVESTIGATION TRAINING?

61
00:03:59,807 --> 00:04:01,672
IT'S JUST SOMETHING
I PICKED UP AS A KID.
LIEUTENANT--

62
00:04:01,741 --> 00:04:04,175
KIMBRALL. MOLLY KIMBRALL.
I'M WITH THE PROVOST
MARSHAL'S OFFICE.

63
00:04:04,244 --> 00:04:07,345
JAROD STEVENS.
YEAH, I KNOW.

64
00:04:07,414 --> 00:04:09,681
THE BASE'S GRAPEVINE
IS PRETTY MUCH SIZZLING...

65
00:04:09,750 --> 00:04:11,949
WITH WORD THAT C.I.D.'S HERE
INVESTIGATING RION'S SUICIDE.

66
00:04:12,018 --> 00:04:16,688
<i>COLONEL DANCE ASSIGNED ME TO</i>
<i>ESCORT YOU AROUND. HE WANTS TO</i>
<i>SEE YOU IN HIS OFFICE A.S.A.P.</i>

67
00:04:16,757 --> 00:04:18,824
<i> HE'S A LITTLE PISSED.</i>
PISSED?

68
00:04:18,892 --> 00:04:21,259
TICKED OFF.

69
00:04:21,327 --> 00:04:23,929
- YOU KNOW, MAD?
- WHY SHOULD HE BE MAD?

70
00:04:23,997 --> 00:04:26,965
I'VE ONLY KEPT HIM WAITING
72 HOURS AND 13 MINUTES.

71
00:04:27,034 --> 00:04:30,268
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>I AM HONORED YOU FINALLY DECIDED</i>
<i>TO PAY ME A VISIT,</i>

72
00:04:30,337 --> 00:04:32,504
EVEN IF IT DID TAKE YOU
THREE AND A HALF DAYS.

73
00:04:32,573 --> 00:04:35,340
I WAS JUST DOING
A LITTLE RECON, TRYING
TO BE A GOOD SOLDIER.

74
00:04:35,409 --> 00:04:38,776
<i> THAT'S AN UNDERSTATEMENT.</i>
<i> TOP 10 IN YOUR CLASS</i>
<i> AT WEST POINT.</i>

75
00:04:38,845 --> 00:04:41,279
J.D. WITH HONORS.
GEORGETOWN LAW.

76
00:04:41,348 --> 00:04:44,015
AND I SAW<i> RAMBO</i> 27 TIMES.

77
00:04:46,587 --> 00:04:49,454
CAPTAIN SAUNDERS HERE
IS THE LEADER
OF RION'S TRAINING UNIT.

78
00:04:49,523 --> 00:04:52,390
HE WAS THERE THE NIGHT HE DIED.
WE'LL BE DOING
SOME TALKING, CAPTAIN.

79
00:04:52,459 --> 00:04:57,328
- MOST DEFINITELY.
- YOUR FILE TELLS ME DAMN NEAR
EVERYTHING EXCEPT YOUR RANK.

80
00:04:57,397 --> 00:04:59,697
I DON'T EVEN KNOW IF YOU'RE
SUPPOSED TO CALL ME "SIR."

81
00:04:59,766 --> 00:05:02,701
WELL, THAT IS THE ARMY.
NOT ONLY DOES IT
PROMOTE THE INCOMPETENT,

82
00:05:02,770 --> 00:05:06,471
<i> BUT IT ALLOWS</i>
<i> C.I.D. OFFICERS LIKE MYSELF</i>
<i> TO KICK AROUND ANYONE...</i>

83
00:05:06,539 --> 00:05:09,140
<i> FROM A PRIVATE TO A GENERAL</i>
<i> REGARDLESS OF RANK.</i>

84
00:05:09,209 --> 00:05:11,576
BUT IF IT MAKES YOU
FEEL ANY BETTER,
I'LL CALL YOU "SIR."

85
00:05:11,645 --> 00:05:14,312
WOULD YOU EXCUSE US FOR NOW?

86
00:05:14,381 --> 00:05:17,015
GLADLY, COLONEL.

87
00:05:17,083 --> 00:05:20,652
LET ME KNOW IF THERE'S
ANYTHING I CAN DO TO HELP,
SIR.

88
00:05:23,423 --> 00:05:26,525
AFTER YOU, LIEUTENANT.

89
00:05:28,462 --> 00:05:31,629
<i>OKAY, STEVENS, LET'S JUST STOP</i>
<i>ALL THIS NICE CRAP.</i>

90
00:05:31,698 --> 00:05:33,631
AGREED?
FAIR ENOUGH.

91
00:05:33,700 --> 00:05:36,834
P.O.W. SURVIVAL TRAINING
IS ABOUT THE SYSTEMATIC
BREAKING DOWN...

92
00:05:36,903 --> 00:05:40,238
OF A MAN'S PSYCHE,
HIS IDENTITY,
EVEN HIS WILL TO LIVE.

93
00:05:40,307 --> 00:05:42,708
IT'S ABOUT SURVIVAL.
NOW, IT IS MY DUTY...

94
00:05:42,776 --> 00:05:45,343
TO SEE WHO CAN AND CANNOT
PASS THAT TEST.

95
00:05:45,412 --> 00:05:48,780
IF A MAN FAILS HERE,
HE GOES DOWN ALONE.

96
00:05:48,849 --> 00:05:52,517
BUT IF HE FAILS THAT TEST
IN WAR, HE TAKES
HIS BROTHERS DOWN WITH HIM.

97
00:05:52,586 --> 00:05:56,254
NOW, THAT'S ALL VERY NOBLE,
BUT LET ME TELL YOU
ABOUT MY DUTY, COLONEL.

98
00:05:56,323 --> 00:05:58,623
YOUR DUTY IS AKIN
TO A SNAKE IN THE GRASS.

99
00:05:58,692 --> 00:06:01,292
AROUND HERE, WE PROTECT
AND POLICE OUR OWN.

100
00:06:01,361 --> 00:06:04,496
WE DON'T NEED SOME
PENTAGON COPPERHEAD
SLITHERING AROUND OUR FEET.

101
00:06:04,565 --> 00:06:07,732
MAYBE THE LATE
WARRANT OFFICER RION DOES.

102
00:06:09,836 --> 00:06:13,104
RION'S DEATH WAS
INVESTIGATED THOROUGHLY.

103
00:06:13,173 --> 00:06:16,374
HE WAS IN THE HOLE
DURING P.O.W. TRAINING,
AND HE SNAPPED.

104
00:06:16,443 --> 00:06:18,810
- AND MUTILATED
AND HUNG HIMSELF.
- HE SNAPPED!

105
00:06:21,014 --> 00:06:23,781
NOW, ANY FURTHER INVESTIGATION
WILL BE A WASTE OF YOUR TIME...

106
00:06:23,850 --> 00:06:25,950
AND, MORE IMPORTANTLY,
MINE.

107
00:06:26,019 --> 00:06:29,654
RION'S PARENTS ARE CONVINCED
THAT THEIR SON'S DEATH
WAS NOT A SUICIDE.

108
00:06:29,723 --> 00:06:32,490
THEY CAN'T ACCEPT THE FACT
THAT SCOTT KILLED HIMSELF.

109
00:06:32,559 --> 00:06:35,059
NOW, IT AIN'T PRETTY,
BUT IT IS TRUE.

110
00:06:35,128 --> 00:06:38,896
THE TRUTH IS EXACTLY
WHAT I INTEND TO FIND OUT,

111
00:06:40,900 --> 00:06:42,901
SIR.

112
00:06:47,507 --> 00:06:49,274
<i>♪♪ [ Classical ]</i>

113
00:06:54,848 --> 00:06:57,348
[ Chuckles ]
WHOA.

114
00:06:59,185 --> 00:07:02,954
YES, I'M STUDYING THE IMPACT
OF UNIQUE PHYSICAL
CHARACTERISTICS...

115
00:07:03,023 --> 00:07:05,156
ON SENSORY PROCESSING.

116
00:07:05,225 --> 00:07:08,026
I WOULD HAVE GUESSED THAT.
THERE'S SOMETHING WEIRD...

117
00:07:08,095 --> 00:07:10,695
ABOUT THIS SHIPPING INVOICE
THAT JAROD LEFT
AT HIS LAST LAIR.

118
00:07:10,763 --> 00:07:13,365
WEIRD HOW?
<i>IT'S SUCH AN OBVIOUS CLUE.</i>

119
00:07:13,433 --> 00:07:17,034
IT'S LIKE JAROD WANTED MISS
PARKER AND MR. LYLE TO GO DOWN
TO TEXAS AND INVESTIGATE IT.

120
00:07:17,103 --> 00:07:19,437
<i> MAYBE HE DID.</i>
<i> WHAT ELSE DID JAROD LEAVE?</i>

121
00:07:19,505 --> 00:07:22,107
<i>SOME ARMY STUFF--</i>
<i>MANUALS, BOOKS, EQUIPMENT.</i>

122
00:07:22,175 --> 00:07:24,509
A-- A WORN-OUT<i> RAMBO</i> VIDEO.
BUT THERE'S JUST SO MUCH STUFF,

123
00:07:24,578 --> 00:07:26,511
I HAVEN'T HAD TIME
TO GO THROUGH IT ALL YET.

124
00:07:26,580 --> 00:07:28,646
<i> WE NEED TO ALERT</i>
<i> MISS PARKER AND LYLE,</i>

125
00:07:28,715 --> 00:07:31,316
AS THIS MAY BE RELEVANT
TO THEIR INVESTIGATION.

126
00:07:31,384 --> 00:07:33,952
THAT'S THE OTHER WEIRD PART.
NO ONE'S HEARD FROM THEM YET.

127
00:07:34,020 --> 00:07:36,287
<i>IT'S LIKE THEY JUST VANISHED.</i>

128
00:07:36,356 --> 00:07:38,456
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>
<i>I CAN'T GET A SIGNAL OUT</i>
<i>THROUGH THESE WALLS.</i>

129
00:07:38,524 --> 00:07:40,525
SCREW SIGNALS.

130
00:07:42,762 --> 00:07:45,730
WHY DON'T YOU JUST
POINT IT AT MY HEAD? HUH?
DON'T TEMPT ME.

131
00:07:45,799 --> 00:07:49,734
WHAT THE HELL KIND OF GAME
IS JAROD PLAYING ANYWAY?
HMM. LET'S SEE.

132
00:07:49,803 --> 00:07:53,471
HE LOCKS US
BOTH IN HERE TOGETHER
FOR GOD KNOWS HOW LONG...

133
00:07:53,540 --> 00:07:56,842
<i> WITH NOTHING BUT</i>
<i> A BUCKET OF STAGNANT WATER</i>
<i> AND A ROLL OF TOILET PAPER.</i>

134
00:07:56,910 --> 00:08:01,846
IT DOESN'T TAKE MUCH TIME
TO FIGURE OUT THIS ISN'T
JUST A GAME OF SURVIVAL.

135
00:08:01,915 --> 00:08:03,914
THIS IS SURVIVAL
OF THE FITTEST.

136
00:08:05,952 --> 00:08:07,886
<i>[ Mr. Lyle ]</i>
<i>WELL, AT LEAST</i>
<i>HE'S NOT A COMPLETE JERK.</i>

137
00:08:07,955 --> 00:08:09,888
HE LEFT US SOME ARMY RATIONS.

138
00:08:09,957 --> 00:08:13,491
-<i> [ Monitor Beeps ]</i>
- MISS PARKER. MR. LYLE.

139
00:08:13,559 --> 00:08:15,593
<i>WELCOME TO YOUR HOME</i>
<i>AWAY FROM HOME.</i>

140
00:08:15,662 --> 00:08:18,329
REVISE THAT LAST STATEMENT.
HE IS A COMPLETE JERK.

141
00:08:18,398 --> 00:08:20,698
FOR ALL THE YEARS THAT I WAS
LOCKED AWAY AT THE CENTRE,

142
00:08:20,767 --> 00:08:24,736
AND FOR THE THREE YEARS
I'VE BEEN OUT, THE KEY
TO MY LIFE HAS BEEN SURVIVAL.

143
00:08:24,805 --> 00:08:27,271
<i> A FUN LITTLE GAME.</i>
<i> NOW ASK YOURSELVES,</i>

144
00:08:27,341 --> 00:08:29,407
WHAT WOULD YOU DO TO SURVIVE?

145
00:08:29,475 --> 00:08:32,944
<i>I FOUND IT'S IMPORTANT</i>
<i>TO KNOW YOURSELF</i>
<i>AND TO KNOW YOUR FAMILY.</i>

146
00:08:33,013 --> 00:08:35,547
HAVE A GOOD TIME.
OH, BY THE WAY,

147
00:08:35,615 --> 00:08:38,382
I'VE WHIPPED YOU UP
A YUMMY LITTLE MEAL.

148
00:08:38,451 --> 00:08:40,385
HOPE YOU ENJOY IT.

149
00:08:46,693 --> 00:08:49,294
MMM-MMM!
BARBECUED GRASSHOPPERS.

150
00:08:49,362 --> 00:08:51,296
[ Chuckles ]

151
00:08:54,734 --> 00:08:57,101
<i>BON APPÉTIT.</i>

152
00:08:59,706 --> 00:09:02,973
ACTUALLY,
THEY'RE SUPPOSED TO BE
VERY HIGH IN PROTEIN.

153
00:09:08,148 --> 00:09:11,249
TASTES LIKE LIQUORICE.

154
00:09:11,317 --> 00:09:15,954
WHAT ABOUT YOU?
WHAT ARE YOU WILLING TO DO
TO SURVIVE, MISS PARKER?

155
00:09:18,191 --> 00:09:19,991
[ Gulps ]

156
00:09:30,303 --> 00:09:32,337
MMM.

157
00:09:38,578 --> 00:09:42,280
OH! OH!
[ Spits ]
<i> [ Object Clatters ]</i>

158
00:09:42,349 --> 00:09:44,682
<i> A KEY.</i>

159
00:09:44,751 --> 00:09:46,818
CLEVER.

160
00:09:46,886 --> 00:09:50,388
<i>ANOTHER LITTLE PIECE</i>
<i>TO WOLFGANG PUKE'S PUZZLE.</i>

161
00:09:52,225 --> 00:09:55,526
I THINK I CHIPPED MY TOOTH.
GREAT. WHAT NEXT?

162
00:09:55,595 --> 00:09:58,028
<i>[ Beeping ]</i>

163
00:10:22,188 --> 00:10:25,289
[ Jarod ]
SO YOU'VE BEEN HERE EVER SINCE
O.C.S. AND M.P. SCHOOL?

164
00:10:25,358 --> 00:10:29,393
YOU READ MY FILE.
I'M C.I.D.
I'M SUPPOSED TO SNOOP.

165
00:10:29,462 --> 00:10:32,864
YOU'RE A VERY CAPABLE OFFICER.
SHOULDN'T YOU HAVE
YOUR BARS BY NOW?

166
00:10:32,932 --> 00:10:38,103
THE REASON I'M NOT A CAPTAIN YET
HAS LESS TO DO WITH ABILITY
THAN IT DOES WITH BIOLOGY.

167
00:10:38,171 --> 00:10:40,572
IT'S NOT EASY TO BE A WOMAN
IN THIS MAN'S ARMY, HUH?

168
00:10:43,009 --> 00:10:44,976
CHIEF RION
USED TO REMIND ME THAT.

169
00:10:45,045 --> 00:10:47,545
- YOU KNEW RION PRETTY WELL?
- WE WERE FRIENDS.

170
00:10:47,614 --> 00:10:51,015
HE TREATED ME WITH RESPECT,
NOT LIKE SOME OF
THESE GUNG-HO IDIOTS.

171
00:10:51,084 --> 00:10:54,752
<i> HE WAS NICE.</i>
<i> REALLY NICE.</i>

172
00:10:57,090 --> 00:11:00,057
IS IT TRUE HE CALLED
HIS PARENTS THE NIGHT BEFORE
HE STARTED P.O.W. TRAINING?

173
00:11:00,126 --> 00:11:02,060
I'M THE ONE WHO'S SUPPOSED
TO SNOOP, REMEMBER?

174
00:11:02,129 --> 00:11:05,196
SORRY. IT'S JUST RUMOR IS,

175
00:11:05,265 --> 00:11:08,767
HE TOLD HIS FATHER THAT
SOMEONE ON BASE COMMITTED
A BREACH OF CONDUCT,

176
00:11:08,835 --> 00:11:12,637
WHICH HE WAS GOING TO REPORT
WHEN HE GOT BACK FROM
THE P.O.W. ISOLATION TEST.

177
00:11:12,705 --> 00:11:15,105
I GUESS HE NEVER GOT THE CHANCE
TO MAKE THAT REPORT, DID HE?

178
00:11:16,176 --> 00:11:18,109
NO, SIR.
I GUESS NOT.

179
00:11:19,312 --> 00:11:21,245
<i>THE TRAINING AREA'S</i>
<i>JUST UP THE ROAD,</i>

180
00:11:21,314 --> 00:11:25,683
BUT I DOUBT YOU'LL FIND
SERGEANT REED ANY MORE HELPFUL
THAN COLONEL DANCE WAS.

181
00:11:25,752 --> 00:11:29,954
SEALY, SEALY, SEALY.

182
00:11:30,023 --> 00:11:31,956
<i> SEALY!</i>

183
00:11:32,025 --> 00:11:35,192
IT'S HOT OUT HERE,
ISN'T IT, SEALY?

184
00:11:36,897 --> 00:11:39,463
[ Sighs ]
THAT SURE HIT THE SPOT.
YOU WANT SOME?

185
00:11:39,532 --> 00:11:41,532
<i> WANT A SIP? HUH?</i>

186
00:11:45,972 --> 00:11:49,741
DAMN, I'VE BEEN
DOIN' THAT ALL DAY.

187
00:11:49,809 --> 00:11:52,810
HANG TOUGH, AIRBORNE.
DON'T CRACK, SEALY!

188
00:11:52,879 --> 00:11:54,778
ALL YOU GOTTA DO
IS QUIT, SEALY.

189
00:11:54,847 --> 00:11:56,647
<i>[ Car Door Closes ]</i>
<i>QUIT.</i>

190
00:11:56,716 --> 00:11:59,284
<i>YOU CAN GO OVER THERE</i>
<i>AND DRINK AS MUCH AS YOU WANT.</i>

191
00:11:59,352 --> 00:12:03,321
WE'LL TAKE YOU BACK TO YOUR
NICE, AIR-CONDITIONED ROOM.
TAKE A NICE, LONG, COLD SHOWER.

192
00:12:03,389 --> 00:12:06,991
AND AFTER THAT,
YOU GET TO CALL YOUR MOMMY,

193
00:12:07,060 --> 00:12:11,061
TELL HER TO COME PICK YOU UP
AT THE AIRPORT
ON THE FIRST FLIGHT HOME!

194
00:12:11,130 --> 00:12:13,130
IS THAT WHAT YOU WANT,
SEALY?
I'M NOT GIVING UP, SERGEANT.

195
00:12:14,634 --> 00:12:18,136
<i>HANG TOUGH, SEALY.</i>
<i>DON'T CRACK!</i>

196
00:12:18,204 --> 00:12:22,139
MR. C.I.D.
STEP INTO MY OFFICE.

197
00:12:22,208 --> 00:12:24,908
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>DON'T GIVE UP!</i>

198
00:12:30,450 --> 00:12:33,451
I UNDERSTAND THAT
YOU WERE IN CHARGE OF TRAINING
THE NIGHT THAT CHIEF RION DIED.

199
00:12:33,519 --> 00:12:35,453
NOT ONLY THAT,
BUT I'M THE ONE...

200
00:12:35,522 --> 00:12:37,955
WHO OPENED UP THE HOLE
AND FOUND HIM
HANGING BY HIS BELT.

201
00:12:38,024 --> 00:12:39,957
IT'S ALL IN THE REPORT.

202
00:12:40,026 --> 00:12:41,926
YOU MUST AT LEAST
HAVE A THEORY
ABOUT WHAT HAPPENED.

203
00:12:41,994 --> 00:12:44,996
HE WENT IN THERE BY HIMSELF,
STAYED DOWN THERE ALL NIGHT
BY HIMSELF.

204
00:12:45,064 --> 00:12:47,131
WE WERE ALL RIGHT OUTSIDE
THE WHOLE TIME.

205
00:12:47,200 --> 00:12:49,601
BOY MUST'VE BEEN
SCARED OF THE DARK
ALL I CAN FIGURE.

206
00:12:49,669 --> 00:12:51,368
LET HIS MIND
GET THE BEST OF HIM.

207
00:12:51,437 --> 00:12:55,139
ENOUGH TO MUTILATE
AND HANG HIMSELF?
NEVER GOT A CHANCE TO ASK HIM.

208
00:12:56,710 --> 00:13:01,145
YOU HERE TO ARREST ME?
NOT TODAY.

209
00:13:01,214 --> 00:13:03,014
GOOD,
'CAUSE I GOT WORK TO DO.

210
00:13:04,818 --> 00:13:08,286
<i>SEE, THESE BOYS ARE STILL ALIVE.</i>
<i>IT'S MY JOB TO KEEP IT THAT WAY.</i>

211
00:13:42,756 --> 00:13:45,356
<i>[ Rion's Voice ]</i>
<i>"DEAR MOM AND DAD,</i>
<i> WE'RE ALMOST FINISHED HERE.</i>

212
00:13:45,424 --> 00:13:47,724
<i>"I CAN'T TELL YOU HOW MUCH</i>
<i> THIS OPPORTUNITY MEANS TO ME.</i>

213
00:13:47,793 --> 00:13:50,094
<i>"EVER SINCE I WAS LITTLE,</i>
<i> I'VE WANTED TO BE ON</i>
<i> THE SPECIAL FORCES...</i>

214
00:13:50,163 --> 00:13:52,330
<i>"JUST LIKE DAD WAS.</i>

215
00:13:52,399 --> 00:13:54,565
<i>"OUR TALKS ABOUT HIS EXPERIENCE</i>
<i> AS A P.O.W. IN VIETNAM...</i>

216
00:13:54,634 --> 00:13:56,867
<i>"PREPARED ME FOR WHAT</i>
<i> I HAD TO GO THROUGH</i>
<i> HERE IN TRAINING.</i>

217
00:13:56,936 --> 00:14:00,704
<i>"AND LIKE HE ALWAYS SAID,</i>
<i> THE MOST IMPORTANT</i>
<i> SURVIVAL TOOL IS THE MIND.</i>

218
00:14:00,773 --> 00:14:04,942
<i>"I MISS YOU BOTH VERY MUCH</i>
<i> AND LOOK FORWARD</i>
<i> TO US BEING TOGETHER SOON.</i>

219
00:14:05,011 --> 00:14:07,412
<i>YOUR LOVING SON, SCOTT."</i>

220
00:14:21,728 --> 00:14:24,429
<i>WE SHOULD'VE HEARD SOMETHING</i>
<i>BY NOW. THERE'S BEEN</i>
<i>NO WORD FROM MISS PARKER,</i>

221
00:14:24,497 --> 00:14:27,397
NO WORD FROM MR. LYLE,
NO ANSWER ON THEIR CELL PHONES.

222
00:14:27,466 --> 00:14:30,435
- SYD, I'M GETTIN'
KIND OF FREAKED HERE.
- I'M CONCERNED AS WELL.

223
00:14:30,503 --> 00:14:32,970
YOU THINK THEIR DISAPPEARANCE
HAS SOMETHING TO DO WITH JAROD?

224
00:14:33,039 --> 00:14:37,642
ALL THOSE MILITARY MANUALS
WE FOUND IN HIS LAIR, DON'T THEY
ALL HAVE A SURVIVAL COMPONENT?

225
00:14:37,711 --> 00:14:41,946
- YEAH.
- I'M GOING TO SEND ANOTHER
SWEEPER TEAM TO TEXAS.

226
00:14:42,014 --> 00:14:46,350
<i>BROOTS, DIG DEEPER INTO</i>
<i>THAT SHIPPING MANIFEST AND</i>
<i>ALL THE OTHER ITEMS WE FOUND.</i>

227
00:14:46,419 --> 00:14:49,787
OKAY, I'M ON IT
LIKE A CHEAP SUIT.

228
00:14:50,857 --> 00:14:53,624
WHAT ARE YOU UP TO,
JAROD?

229
00:14:53,693 --> 00:14:57,428
<i> SOME P.O.W.s RETURNED FROM</i>
<i> THE BRUTALITY AND ISOLATION</i>
<i> OF PRISON CAMP INTACT,</i>

230
00:14:57,497 --> 00:15:01,565
OTHERS AS MERE SHADOWS
OF THE MAN THEY ONCE WERE.

231
00:15:01,634 --> 00:15:03,934
[ Young Jarod ]
THEY SEEM HAUNTED.
YOU'RE RIGHT.

232
00:15:04,003 --> 00:15:06,037
<i>[ Young Sydney ]</i>
<i>STUDY THESE MEN, JAROD.</i>

233
00:15:06,105 --> 00:15:09,640
<i>HELP US UNDERSTAND WHY</i>
<i>SOME SURVIVE AND SOME SHATTER.</i>

234
00:15:39,639 --> 00:15:41,906
<i> [ Knocking ]</i>
COME IN.

235
00:15:41,975 --> 00:15:43,874
I FOUND CAP--

236
00:15:43,943 --> 00:15:48,012
<i> CAPTAIN SAUNDERS</i>
<i> AND THE REST OF</i>
<i> CHIEF RION'S UNIT,</i>

237
00:15:48,080 --> 00:15:50,014
SORT OF.
WHERE?

238
00:15:50,083 --> 00:15:52,850
WELL, THEY FINISHED
THE P.O.W. PHASE
OF THEIR TRAINING...

239
00:15:52,919 --> 00:15:56,053
AND HEADED OUT
TO THE SOUTH RANGE
FOR SOME KIND OF INITIATION.

240
00:15:56,122 --> 00:15:58,055
INITIATION?
YEAH.

241
00:15:58,124 --> 00:16:00,725
THEY COULD BE ANYWHERE
IN THIS 50-SQUARE-MILE AREA.

242
00:16:00,793 --> 00:16:02,694
WELL, I GUESS I BETTER
BRING MY CANTEEN.

243
00:16:02,762 --> 00:16:07,731
UM, NOTHING PERSONAL, SIR,
BUT YOU'LL NEVER FIND THEM.

244
00:16:07,800 --> 00:16:12,837
THEY ARE EXPERTS.
THEY JUST GO OUT THERE
AND DISAPPEAR.

245
00:16:37,697 --> 00:16:40,131
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>BRAND'S READY, CAPTAIN SAUNDERS.</i>

246
00:16:40,200 --> 00:16:42,133
YOU'VE EARNED IT, SOLDIER.

247
00:16:42,202 --> 00:16:44,568
GIVE ME THE BOTTLE.
TAKE A HIT.

248
00:16:49,375 --> 00:16:51,475
- YOU READY?
- I'M READY, SIR.

249
00:17:04,957 --> 00:17:07,424
WHOO! YEAH!
YOU DID IT, MAN!
YOU DID IT!

250
00:17:07,493 --> 00:17:09,626
<i> IS THIS WHAT THEY CALL</i>
<i> A WEENIE ROAST?</i>

251
00:17:11,364 --> 00:17:14,398
- HOW THE HELL
DID YOU FIND US, C.I.D.?
- I FOLLOWED YOUR TRACKS.

252
00:17:14,467 --> 00:17:17,301
- WE DON'T LEAVE TRACKS,
STEVENS.
- CALL THEM WHAT YOU WILL.

253
00:17:17,369 --> 00:17:20,170
BUT THERE WAS
A PRESSURE INDENTATION
BY THE CREEK BED,

254
00:17:20,239 --> 00:17:22,172
A STONE WAS KICKED OVER
BY THE OUTCROPPING,

255
00:17:22,241 --> 00:17:25,342
AND SOMEONE WITH A SIZE
11-AND-A-HALF BOOT
HAS A CRACK IN THEIR HEEL.

256
00:17:25,411 --> 00:17:28,145
<i> SENDING UP A FLARE</i>
<i> WOULD HAVE BEEN</i>
<i> LESS CONSPICUOUS.</i>

257
00:17:28,214 --> 00:17:31,148
YOU KNOW, I'D BE CAREFUL
WHO THE HELL YOU'RE
SNEAKIN' UP ON, C.I.D.

258
00:17:31,217 --> 00:17:33,950
AND I'D BE CAREFUL
ABOUT VIOLATING REGULATIONS.

259
00:17:35,755 --> 00:17:38,856
THIS IS TRADITION,
AND IT'S VOLUNTARY.

260
00:17:38,925 --> 00:17:42,359
RIGHT, SEALY?
YES, SIR.

261
00:17:42,428 --> 00:17:45,429
DEMOLITIONS MAN.

262
00:17:45,497 --> 00:17:49,366
- YES, SIR.
- YOU DON'T FIND THAT VERY OFTEN
IN SURVIVAL TRAINING.

263
00:17:49,435 --> 00:17:51,368
WE ALL COME FROM
DIFFERENT DISCIPLINES.

264
00:17:51,437 --> 00:17:54,204
I WAS A MEDICAL OFFICER,
COUNTERINTELLIGENCE.

265
00:17:54,273 --> 00:17:58,175
RION WAS LOGISTICS.
DUVALL HERE TOOK HIS PLACE.

266
00:17:58,244 --> 00:18:02,379
AND WALKER'S OUR WEAPONS EXPERT.
DIFFERENT DISCIPLINES,
ONE MIND, BODY AND SOUL.

267
00:18:02,448 --> 00:18:07,150
- WE TRAIN TO BECOME A TEAM.
- SO YOU ALL KNEW SCOTT RION
PRETTY WELL.

268
00:18:07,219 --> 00:18:09,486
<i>WHEN YOUR TRAINING'S</i>
<i>ABOUT SURVIVAL,</i>
<i>IT'S AS IMPORTANT...</i>

269
00:18:09,555 --> 00:18:12,255
TO GET TO KNOW YOUR FRIENDS
AS IT IS TO GET
TO KNOW YOUR ENEMIES.

270
00:18:12,324 --> 00:18:16,127
- YOUR LIFE DEPENDS ON IT, SIR.
- A WHOLE LOT OF GOOD
THAT DID SCOTT RION.

271
00:18:16,195 --> 00:18:19,029
- SCOTT HAD HIS OWN PROBLEMS.
- WHAT KIND?

272
00:18:19,098 --> 00:18:21,198
PERSONAL. IN FACT, I SENSED
HE WAS FALLIN' APART.

273
00:18:21,266 --> 00:18:24,368
<i>THERE WERE TIMES</i>
<i>I EVEN COVERED FOR HIM</i>
<i>DURING TRAINING.</i>

274
00:18:27,273 --> 00:18:30,407
LOOK, I WANTED RION
TO MAKE IT.

275
00:18:30,476 --> 00:18:33,977
WE ALL...
WANTED RION TO MAKE IT.

276
00:18:34,046 --> 00:18:37,348
<i>AND I GUESS I SHOULD'VE</i>
<i>GONE TO THE COLONEL, BUT I WAS</i>
<i>AFRAID HE'D KICK RION OUT.</i>

277
00:18:37,417 --> 00:18:41,084
MAYBE IF I HAD,
HE'D STILL BE ALIVE.

278
00:18:41,153 --> 00:18:43,353
WELL, LIKE YOU SAID,

279
00:18:43,422 --> 00:18:46,924
IT'S AS IMPORTANT
TO KNOW YOUR FRIENDS...

280
00:18:46,993 --> 00:18:49,326
AS IT IS
TO KNOW YOUR ENEMIES.

281
00:18:53,465 --> 00:18:56,467
<i> [ Horn Honking ]</i>

282
00:18:56,535 --> 00:18:58,502
<i> [ Mr. Lyle ]</i>
<i> WE NEED FLUIDS,</i>
<i> OR WE'LL DEHYDRATE.</i>

283
00:18:58,571 --> 00:19:00,604
THIS TOOTH'LL KILL ME
BEFORE THEN.

284
00:19:00,673 --> 00:19:03,941
WHEN IT COMES TO SURVIVAL,
JAROD DOESN'T KNOW
THE FIRST THING ABOUT ME.

285
00:19:05,511 --> 00:19:08,011
TOO BAD YOU QUIT SMOKING.

286
00:19:08,080 --> 00:19:09,913
GIVE IT UP, DANIEL BOONE.

287
00:19:12,284 --> 00:19:14,751
BRR! I BET IT'S GETTING
PRETTY COLD IN THERE.

288
00:19:14,820 --> 00:19:18,055
<i> I HOPE YOU TWO ARE</i>
<i> GETTING ALONG OKAY.</i>
<i> YOU KNOW WHAT THEY SAY:</i>

289
00:19:18,124 --> 00:19:21,492
WHEN OPPOSITE POLARITIES
COME TOGETHER, THINGS
CAN GET HOT PRETTY QUICKLY.

290
00:19:21,560 --> 00:19:25,629
<i>OH, IN CASE ANYBODY'S</i>
<i>INTERESTED, THERE'S A TUBE</i>
<i>OF ANBESOL IN THERE SOMEWHERE.</i>

291
00:19:25,697 --> 00:19:27,932
SEARCHING FOR IT
CAN KEEP YOU WARM.

292
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:32,402
NO. MATCHES FOR A FIRE
WOULD KEEP ME WARM.

293
00:19:32,471 --> 00:19:34,638
SHUT UP
AND FIND THE ANBESOL.

294
00:19:41,480 --> 00:19:43,547
"OPPOSITE POLARITIES."

295
00:19:49,655 --> 00:19:52,656
OH, GREAT.
WE'LL SUFFOCATE.

296
00:20:01,968 --> 00:20:05,569
FOUND THE ANBESOL.
I BET YOU'RE GLAD
I'M HERE NOW.

297
00:20:05,638 --> 00:20:08,738
YOU CAN THANK ME LATER.
WE'RE GONNA CHOKE
ON THE SMOKE...

298
00:20:08,807 --> 00:20:10,808
<i> IF I DON'T GET</i>
<i> THIS THING SEALED.</i>

299
00:20:12,911 --> 00:20:16,780
I NEED... DUCT TAPE.

300
00:20:16,849 --> 00:20:19,116
PERFECT.

301
00:20:19,184 --> 00:20:22,086
<i>GOTTA HAND IT TO JAROD.</i>
<i>[ Tape Ripping ]</i>

302
00:20:22,154 --> 00:20:25,289
<i>THEY SAY DUCT TAPE</i>
<i>IS THE BEST THING TO HAVE...</i>

303
00:20:25,357 --> 00:20:27,258
IN A SURVIVAL SITUATION.

304
00:20:27,326 --> 00:20:30,427
<i> VERY CLEVER.</i>
<i> [ Tape Ripping ]</i>

305
00:20:37,736 --> 00:20:40,770
BUT HE'S NOT AS CLEVER
OR SMART AS HE THINKS HE IS.

306
00:20:43,075 --> 00:20:45,709
FEW PEOPLE ARE.

307
00:21:41,166 --> 00:21:43,100
<i>[ Kimbrall ]</i>
<i>WHAT ARE YOU DOIN' HERE</i>
<i>SO LATE?</i>

308
00:21:43,168 --> 00:21:47,437
I WAS GOING OVER FILES
IN COLONEL DANCE'S OFFICE.
AFTER MIDNIGHT?

309
00:21:47,506 --> 00:21:50,440
WELL, I GUESS YOU DIDN'T
GET THE MEMO ON THE COLONEL'S
NEW "OPEN DOOR" POLICY.

310
00:21:50,509 --> 00:21:53,043
YOU DO LIKE TO
RUFFLE FEATHERS, DON'T YOU?

311
00:21:53,112 --> 00:21:55,345
HOP IN.
I'LL GIVE YOU A RIDE HOME.

312
00:21:57,583 --> 00:21:59,950
GET OUT OF THE CAR.
GET OUT OF THE CAR!

313
00:22:27,980 --> 00:22:31,314
<i>[ Animal Howling ]</i>

314
00:22:35,121 --> 00:22:37,654
<i> TAKING A STROLL DOWN</i>
<i> MEMORY LANE, SEALY?</i>

315
00:22:37,723 --> 00:22:40,991
YOU SCARED ME, STEVENS.
<i> WELL, THERE'S A LOT OF THAT</i>
<i> GOING AROUND TONIGHT.</i>

316
00:22:41,060 --> 00:22:45,195
SOMEBODY TRIED TO BLOW UP
ME AND LIEUTENANT KIMBRALL.

317
00:22:45,263 --> 00:22:47,965
SOMEBODY WHO KNOWS THEIR WAY
AROUND A FIRECRACKER.

318
00:22:48,033 --> 00:22:52,002
IT WASN'T ME.
IF IT HAD HAVE BEEN, THEY'D
BE MOPPING YOU UP ABOUT NOW.

319
00:22:52,071 --> 00:22:54,738
I SEE. SO,
YOU HAVING TROUBLE SLEEPING?

320
00:22:54,806 --> 00:22:57,974
I JUST THOUGHT
I'D TAKE A WALK.

321
00:22:58,043 --> 00:23:01,678
TO THE PLACE
WHERE CHIEF RION DIED.
INTERESTING.

322
00:23:03,215 --> 00:23:05,149
YOU CAN STILL HEAR HIM,
CAN'T YOU?

323
00:23:05,217 --> 00:23:09,486
<i> HIS SCREAMS.</i>
<i> HIS PAIN.</i>

324
00:23:09,555 --> 00:23:12,556
I WAS HERE WHEN IT HAPPENED.

325
00:23:13,693 --> 00:23:15,626
IT WAS HIS LAST NIGHT
IN THE HOLE.

326
00:23:15,694 --> 00:23:18,161
HE WAS DOWN THERE
HOWLIN' AND SCREAMIN'
ALL NIGHT,

327
00:23:18,230 --> 00:23:21,131
CALLIN' OUT
CAPTAIN SAUNDERS'S NAME...

328
00:23:21,199 --> 00:23:23,200
AND YELLIN' ALL KINDS
OF CRAZY STUFF.

329
00:23:23,269 --> 00:23:25,568
[ Groaning ]

330
00:23:27,773 --> 00:23:30,640
[ Yelling ]

331
00:23:33,812 --> 00:23:36,647
<i>IT WAS HORRIBLE LISTENING</i>
<i>TO HIM THE WHOLE NIGHT.</i>

332
00:23:38,584 --> 00:23:41,818
THEN AROUND DAYBREAK,
IT JUST STOPPED.

333
00:23:41,887 --> 00:23:45,155
<i> I THOUGHT HE PASSED OUT</i>
<i> TILL SERGEANT REED</i>
<i> OPENED THE DOOR,</i>

334
00:23:45,224 --> 00:23:47,224
AND WE SAW HIM...

335
00:23:48,627 --> 00:23:51,361
HANGING FROM THE CEILING.

336
00:23:51,430 --> 00:23:55,665
HE'D GONE AND SCRATCHED HIMSELF
ALL UP. IT WAS LIKE SOMETHING
OUT OF A HORROR MOVIE.

337
00:23:55,734 --> 00:23:59,136
<i> I DON'T KNOW WHO OR WHAT</i>
<i> COULD CAUSE SOMEONE</i>
<i> TO FLIP OUT LIKE THAT.</i>

338
00:23:59,204 --> 00:24:01,071
I SWEAR I DON'T.

339
00:24:01,140 --> 00:24:04,641
WHY DIDN'T YOU GET HIM OUT?
<i> I WANTED TO.</i>
<i> WE ALL DID.</i>

340
00:24:04,710 --> 00:24:07,443
- BUT WE WERE ORDERED NOT TO.
- CAPTAIN SAUNDERS?

341
00:24:07,512 --> 00:24:11,681
<i>AND SERGEANT REED. THEY SAID</i>
<i>IF WE PULLED RION OUT,</i>
<i>HE'D BE KICKED OUT OF TRAINING.</i>

342
00:24:13,218 --> 00:24:16,253
SO THEY JUST LEFT HIM
DOWN THERE TO DIE.

343
00:24:16,321 --> 00:24:18,488
IT'S NOT LIKE THEY KNEW
HE'D KILL HIMSELF.

344
00:24:18,557 --> 00:24:21,491
HOW COULD ANYONE
HAVE KNOWN?

345
00:24:24,230 --> 00:24:28,364
<i>[ Mr. Lyle ]</i>
<i>IT HASN'T BEEN EASY TRYING TO</i>
<i>PUT THE MURDERS OUT OF MY MIND.</i>

346
00:24:28,433 --> 00:24:30,534
LOOKS LIKE YOU'VE DONE
A PRETTY GOOD JOB.

347
00:24:34,873 --> 00:24:38,708
I MET SUE AT
THE UNIVERSITY OF VIRGINIA.

348
00:24:38,777 --> 00:24:42,445
SHE WAS PART OF
AN EXCHANGE PROGRAM
WITH HER SISTER CINDY.

349
00:24:42,514 --> 00:24:45,114
<i>ONE NIGHT,</i>
<i>I STOPPED BY THEIR APARTMENT.</i>
<i>THE DOOR WAS OPEN.</i>

350
00:24:45,183 --> 00:24:49,753
SO I WENT ON IN
AND FOUND 'EM--

351
00:24:49,822 --> 00:24:52,055
WHAT WAS LEFT OF THEM--

352
00:24:52,124 --> 00:24:54,057
<i>IN THE BEDROOM.</i>

353
00:24:54,126 --> 00:24:58,261
<i>I WAS A SUSPECT AT FIRST.</i>
<i>THEN THE POLICE FOUND</i>
<i>A ROLL OF DUCT TAPE...</i>

354
00:24:58,330 --> 00:25:00,630
IN THE TRUNK OF
CINDY'S EX-BOYFRIEND'S CAR.

355
00:25:00,699 --> 00:25:03,967
<i>THE SAME TAPE THAT HAD</i>
<i>BEEN USED ON BOTH SISTERS.</i>

356
00:25:07,239 --> 00:25:11,374
OR MAYBE SOMEONE
PLANTED THE DUCT TAPE
ON AN INNOCENT MAN.

357
00:25:11,443 --> 00:25:14,311
YOU KNOW, TO SURVIVE.

358
00:25:24,056 --> 00:25:27,390
<i>DON'T YOU SEE WHAT</i>
<i>JAROD'S TRYING TO DO?</i>
<i>WHETHER IT'S IN THIS TRAP...</i>

359
00:25:27,459 --> 00:25:30,427
<i>OR AT THE CENTRE,</i>
<i>HE'S TRYING TO KEEP US</i>
<i>FROM TRUSTING EACH OTHER.</i>

360
00:25:30,496 --> 00:25:35,632
YOU'VE GOTTA TRUST ME, PARKER.
IT'S A MUST FOR OUR SURVIVAL.

361
00:25:35,701 --> 00:25:37,634
<i>WHAT'S THAT?</i>

362
00:25:37,702 --> 00:25:39,903
PARKER?

363
00:25:39,972 --> 00:25:42,005
<i>PARKER?</i>

364
00:25:42,074 --> 00:25:44,274
YOU THINK OF EVERYTHING,
DON'T YOU, JAROD?

365
00:25:59,391 --> 00:26:02,893
WHAT'S THE WATCH ABOUT?

366
00:26:02,961 --> 00:26:05,128
SURVIVAL.

367
00:26:06,565 --> 00:26:09,799
<i> SYDNEY! SYD!</i>

368
00:26:09,868 --> 00:26:12,502
THAT SWEEPER TEAM
YOU SENT TO TEXAS--

369
00:26:12,571 --> 00:26:16,139
THEY DIDN'T FIND THEM,
BUT THEY INTERVIEWED SOME BUM...

370
00:26:16,207 --> 00:26:20,476
WHO HAD TAKEN MISS PARKER AND
MR. LYLE TO A SHIPPING CONTAINER
WHERE JAROD HAD BEEN LIVING.

371
00:26:20,545 --> 00:26:23,647
THE SHIPPING CONTAINER--
WAS IT STILL THERE?
OH, NO, IT'S GONE.

372
00:26:23,715 --> 00:26:27,384
I CAN'T FIND IT.
ALL ANYONE SEEMS TO KNOW
IS THAT IT'S HEADING EAST.

373
00:26:27,453 --> 00:26:30,120
ALONG WITH PARKER AND LYLE?
BUT THAT'S NOT ALL.

374
00:26:30,189 --> 00:26:32,122
FOR 10 BUCKS, THE BUM
TOLD THE SWEEPERS THAT...

375
00:26:32,191 --> 00:26:35,024
JAROD HAD TURNED THE CONTAINER
INTO A KIND OF A P.O.W. CAMP,

376
00:26:35,093 --> 00:26:37,027
AND THAT
HE WAS THE PRISONER.

377
00:26:37,096 --> 00:26:38,996
HMM. SURVIVAL.
EXACTLY.

378
00:26:39,064 --> 00:26:41,131
I SIFTED THROUGH EVERYTHING
FROM JAROD'S LAIR.

379
00:26:41,200 --> 00:26:46,002
MOST OF IT IS USED IN TRAINING
AT MILITARY, P.O.W. AND SURVIVAL
UNITS ACROSS THE COUNTRY.

380
00:26:46,071 --> 00:26:48,705
JAROD MAY HAVE BEEN
AT ONE OF THESE FACILITIES.

381
00:26:50,408 --> 00:26:53,477
OR STILL MAY BE.

382
00:26:53,545 --> 00:26:57,347
[ Young Jarod ]
I'VE EVALUATED THE DATA, SYDNEY.
AND WHAT HAVE YOU DETERMINED?

383
00:26:57,416 --> 00:27:00,149
IT'S NOT NECESSARILY
THE PRISONER WHO SUFFERED
THE MOST PHYSICALLY...

384
00:27:00,218 --> 00:27:04,287
OR WERE HELD IN CAPTIVITY
THE LONGEST WHO EXPERIENCED
THE MOST SIGNIFICANT TRAUMA.

385
00:27:04,356 --> 00:27:07,023
THEN WHAT IS
THE CRITICAL FACTOR
TO THEIR SURVIVAL?

386
00:27:07,092 --> 00:27:09,860
[ Young Jarod ]
THEIR MINDS, SYDNEY.

387
00:27:09,929 --> 00:27:12,362
THEIR WILL TO SURVIVE.

388
00:27:12,431 --> 00:27:14,364
IF THE CAPTOR
REMOVES THEIR HOPE,

389
00:27:14,433 --> 00:27:17,400
THEIR ABILITY TO UNDERSTAND
THEIR FEARS AND OVERCOME THEM,

390
00:27:17,469 --> 00:27:20,737
THE PRISONER LOSES
HIS GRIP ON REALITY,
SELF-DESTRUCTS.

391
00:28:10,022 --> 00:28:14,157
[ Imitating Ricky Ricardo ]
LUCY, YOU GOT
SOME EXPLAININ' TO DO.

392
00:28:14,226 --> 00:28:16,826
I SAW THAT ON A RERUN.
THIS ISN'T
WHAT IT LOOKS LIKE.

393
00:28:16,895 --> 00:28:20,663
I HOPE NOT, 'CAUSE
IT SURE DOESN'T LOOK VERY GOOD
TO MY FRIEND OVER HERE.

394
00:28:22,901 --> 00:28:26,303
I CAME HERE TO LOOK
IN CHIEF RION'S FILE.

395
00:28:28,040 --> 00:28:31,240
I CAN'T JUST SIT BACK
AND HOPE THIS ALL GOES AWAY.

396
00:28:31,309 --> 00:28:33,443
I HAVE TO FIND OUT
WHAT REALLY HAPPENED TO SCOTT.

397
00:28:33,512 --> 00:28:36,079
YOU DON'T BELIEVE THAT
IT WAS JUST A SUICIDE EITHER,
DO YOU?

398
00:28:36,147 --> 00:28:38,481
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT TO BELIEVE.

399
00:28:38,550 --> 00:28:41,684
ALL I KNOW IS SCOTT'S FAMILY
DESERVES THE TRUTH.

400
00:28:41,753 --> 00:28:44,754
AND IF THAT MEANS RISKING
MY COMMISSION TO GET IT TO 'EM,
THEN SO BE IT.

401
00:28:44,823 --> 00:28:46,756
WHAT YOU'RE RISKING
IS YOUR LIFE.

402
00:28:46,825 --> 00:28:48,758
THAT BOMB IN YOUR CAR
WASN'T MEANT FOR ME.

403
00:28:51,396 --> 00:28:54,298
WHY DON'T YOU TELL ME
ABOUT CAPTAIN SAUNDERS.

404
00:28:56,235 --> 00:28:58,168
I SEE THE WAY HE LOOKS AT YOU.

405
00:29:02,407 --> 00:29:06,375
WELL, WHEN NO ONE'S AROUND,
HE'S TOUCHED ME...

406
00:29:06,444 --> 00:29:08,278
INAPPROPRIATELY.

407
00:29:08,347 --> 00:29:11,881
- HOW LONG HAS THIS
BEEN GOING ON?
- A FEW MONTHS.

408
00:29:13,418 --> 00:29:15,419
[ Sighs ]

409
00:29:17,056 --> 00:29:20,991
FIRST, IT WAS JUST COMMENTS.
SUGGESTIONS.

410
00:29:21,060 --> 00:29:23,660
YOU GET USED
TO THAT KIND OF CRAP WHEN
YOU'RE A FEMALE IN THE MILITARY.

411
00:29:23,728 --> 00:29:26,530
YOU JUST LEARN TO IGNORE IT
AND HOPE IT STOPS.

412
00:29:26,598 --> 00:29:29,966
- BUT IT DIDN'T?
- NO.

413
00:29:30,035 --> 00:29:32,802
- AND YOU TOLD SCOTT ABOUT IT?
- [ Scoffs ]

414
00:29:32,871 --> 00:29:35,205
I MADE HIM PROMISE
NOT TO TELL ANYONE.

415
00:29:35,274 --> 00:29:37,941
WHAT HAPPENED?

416
00:29:41,680 --> 00:29:45,481
ABOUT A WEEK
BEFORE SCOTT'S DEATH,

417
00:29:45,550 --> 00:29:48,317
I WENT OFF BASE TO MEET
SOME FRIENDS FOR DINNER.

418
00:29:48,386 --> 00:29:51,688
CAPTAIN SAUNDERS WAS THERE,
CHIEF RION,
THE REST OF THE UNIT.

419
00:29:51,757 --> 00:29:55,759
CAPTAIN SAUNDERS
KEPT STARING AT ME...

420
00:29:55,827 --> 00:29:58,495
TO THE POINT THAT
IT WAS SCARING ME.

421
00:29:58,563 --> 00:30:00,530
SO I GOT UP AND LEFT.

422
00:30:00,599 --> 00:30:04,267
<i>I JUST WANTED TO</i>
<i>GET OUT OF THERE AND GO HOME.</i>

423
00:30:04,336 --> 00:30:08,105
<i>CAPTAIN SAUNDERS GRABBED ME.</i>
<i>HE WOULDN'T LET GO.</i>
<i>I TRIED TO FIGHT HIM.</i>

424
00:30:08,173 --> 00:30:10,873
<i>I WAS YELLING AT HIM</i>
<i>TO LET GO OF ME.</i>
GET OFF OF ME!

425
00:30:13,712 --> 00:30:17,981
<i>I WAS SO SCARED.</i>
<i>HE WAS TRYING TO PUSH ME</i>
<i>INTO THE CAR.</i>

426
00:30:18,050 --> 00:30:21,852
<i>THEN, ALL OF THE SUDDEN,</i>
<i>SOMEONE PULLED HIM OFF OF ME.</i>

427
00:30:21,921 --> 00:30:24,054
<i> SCOTT RION.</i>

428
00:30:27,526 --> 00:30:30,127
HE TOLD CAPTAIN SAUNDERS
HE WAS GOING TO REPORT HIM.

429
00:30:30,195 --> 00:30:34,498
<i>THEY ARGUED.</i>
<i>CAPTAIN SAUNDERS TOLD SCOTT</i>
<i>HE'D FORGOTTEN THE FIRST RULE--</i>

430
00:30:34,567 --> 00:30:36,467
THAT THE UNIT
ALWAYS COMES FIRST.

431
00:30:36,535 --> 00:30:39,503
<i>HE SAID IT WASN'T OVER</i>
<i>BETWEEN THEM,</i>

432
00:30:39,571 --> 00:30:42,039
<i>THAT HE'D MAKE SURE</i>
<i>SCOTT LEARNED HIS LESSON.</i>

433
00:30:42,108 --> 00:30:47,878
WHEN SCOTT COMMITTED SUICIDE,
I FELT RESPONSIBLE.

434
00:30:47,947 --> 00:30:52,616
SCOTT DID COMMIT SUICIDE,
BUT IT WASN'T BY CHOICE.

435
00:30:52,685 --> 00:30:55,652
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

436
00:30:55,721 --> 00:31:00,290
HIS PSYCHOLOGICAL PROFILE
SHOWED NO SIGNS OF INSTABILITY.

437
00:31:00,359 --> 00:31:02,793
PRISONER OF WAR TRAINING
IS TOUGH,

438
00:31:02,862 --> 00:31:05,061
BUT SCOTT KNEW HE ONLY HAD
TO ENDURE ONE MORE NIGHT.

439
00:31:05,130 --> 00:31:07,264
THEN WHAT COULD HAVE MADE HIM
GO OUT OF HIS MIND?

440
00:31:07,333 --> 00:31:09,600
SOMETHING I FOUND
<i> IN</i> HIS MIND.

441
00:31:09,669 --> 00:31:12,669
YOU'RE SAYING
HE WAS GIVEN SOMETHING
TO MAKE HIM GO CRAZY?

442
00:31:12,738 --> 00:31:16,573
THAT'S WHAT HE WAS TRYING
TO TELL US.
HE WASN'T MUTILATING HIMSELF.

443
00:31:16,642 --> 00:31:20,711
HE WAS WRITING A WORD.
SCOTT KNEW HE WAS DRUGGED.

444
00:31:20,779 --> 00:31:24,315
HE WAS ATTEMPTING TO TELL US
WHO DID IT AND HOW.

445
00:31:24,383 --> 00:31:26,350
THAT SEEMS SO IMPOSSIBLE.

446
00:31:26,419 --> 00:31:30,054
RION KNEW THAT SAUNDERS
WAS INVOLVED IN A SECRET
RESEARCH PROJECT...

447
00:31:30,122 --> 00:31:33,223
TO DEVELOP DRUGS TO INTERROGATE
PRISONERS OF WAR.

448
00:31:33,292 --> 00:31:35,292
THE NAME OF
THAT PROJECT WAS--

449
00:31:36,728 --> 00:31:38,662
<i>[ Kimbrall ]</i>
<i>"ABYSS."</i>

450
00:31:38,731 --> 00:31:40,964
SCOTT KNEW HE WAS GIVEN
THE ABYSS DRUG.

451
00:31:41,033 --> 00:31:44,601
AS HE BECAME MORE
PSYCHOTIC AND DISORIENTED,

452
00:31:44,670 --> 00:31:46,770
HE ATTEMPTED TO TELL US.

453
00:31:49,108 --> 00:31:51,442
SO WHAT ARE YOU GONNA
DO ABOUT IT?

454
00:31:53,312 --> 00:31:56,413
I'M GOING TO GIVE
CAPTAIN SAUNDERS...

455
00:31:56,482 --> 00:31:59,116
A LITTLE TASTE
OF HIS OWN MEDICINE.

456
00:32:13,832 --> 00:32:16,132
IT'S OKAY TO DRINK NOW.

457
00:32:18,870 --> 00:32:20,471
TRUST ME.

458
00:32:31,316 --> 00:32:35,385
"TICK TOCK."
JAROD WANTED YOU
TO FIND THAT WATCH.

459
00:32:35,454 --> 00:32:38,188
HE KNEW IT MEANT
SOMETHING TO YOU.

460
00:32:38,257 --> 00:32:41,291
IT WAS MY--

461
00:32:41,360 --> 00:32:45,729
<i> OUR</i> MOTHER'S.

462
00:32:51,103 --> 00:32:53,403
SHE WON IT IN A SWIM COMPETITION
WHEN SHE WAS LITTLE,

463
00:32:53,472 --> 00:32:57,574
AND DADDY GAVE IT TO ME
FOR MY 12th BIRTHDAY.

464
00:32:59,712 --> 00:33:02,279
I USED TO USE IT
TO TIME MYSELF...

465
00:33:02,347 --> 00:33:04,647
TREADING WATER WHEN
WE WOULD GO TO THE LAKE.

466
00:33:04,716 --> 00:33:07,150
<i>AND THIS ONE PARTICULAR MORNING,</i>
<i>IT WAS EARLY.</i>

467
00:33:07,219 --> 00:33:11,021
<i>I TOOK THE SKIP OUT ALONE,</i>
<i>AND I WENT WAY OUT</i>
<i>INTO THE MIDDLE.</i>

468
00:33:11,090 --> 00:33:16,059
IT STARTED TAKING ON WATER,
AND BEFORE I COULD MAKE IT BACK,
IT SANK.

469
00:33:16,128 --> 00:33:18,261
AND I TRIED TO SWIM,

470
00:33:18,330 --> 00:33:20,864
BUT IT WAS JUST SO FAR.

471
00:33:20,933 --> 00:33:25,335
ALL I COULD DO WAS TREAD WATER
AND HOPE SOMEONE
WOULD FIND ME.

472
00:33:25,404 --> 00:33:30,507
<i>MY LEGS WERE CRAMPING,</i>
<i>AND MY ARMS WERE ACHING.</i>
<i>IT WAS TERRIFYING.</i>

473
00:33:30,575 --> 00:33:33,477
EVERY TIME I WANTED
TO GIVE IN...

474
00:33:33,545 --> 00:33:37,781
AND TO SURRENDER TO THE PAIN,
TO LET MYSELF SINK,

475
00:33:40,552 --> 00:33:44,622
I WOULD HEAR THE TICKING
OF THIS WATCH.

476
00:33:44,690 --> 00:33:47,124
AND IT WAS LIKE MOTHER'S VOICE
WHISPERING TO ME...

477
00:33:47,192 --> 00:33:49,559
TO FIGHT FOR MY LIFE--

478
00:33:49,629 --> 00:33:51,561
TO FIGHT TO SURVIVE.

479
00:33:53,332 --> 00:33:56,199
AND I DID.

480
00:33:58,137 --> 00:34:01,038
[ Scoffs ]

481
00:34:01,106 --> 00:34:03,439
ANYWAY,

482
00:34:03,508 --> 00:34:06,143
EVENTUALLY DADDY
CAME AND RESCUED ME.

483
00:34:06,211 --> 00:34:10,146
BUT IT WAS THIS WATCH
THAT SAVED MY LIFE.

484
00:34:10,215 --> 00:34:13,716
<i>I LOST IT A LONG TIME AGO.</i>
LOOKS LIKE
SOMEBODY FOUND IT.

485
00:34:18,057 --> 00:34:21,391
<i>[ Engine Shuts Off ]</i>

486
00:34:21,460 --> 00:34:23,994
WHAT NOW?

487
00:35:36,301 --> 00:35:39,569
SYD! SYD!
I FOUND IT.

488
00:35:39,638 --> 00:35:42,672
I FOUND THE CONTAINER,
AND YOU'RE NOT GONNA
BELIEVE WHERE.

489
00:35:43,976 --> 00:35:46,676
<i>[ Pounding ]</i>
<i>[ Broots ]</i>
<i>MISS PARKER? MISS PARKER?</i>

490
00:35:46,745 --> 00:35:50,981
BROOTS?
BROOTS, YOU LOVABLE MORON,
IS THAT YOU?

491
00:35:51,049 --> 00:35:52,983
<i>YEAH, I GUESS.</i>

492
00:35:53,052 --> 00:35:55,753
OPEN THE DOOR!
<i>[ Sydney ]</i>
<i>YOU'LL HAVE TO DO IT.</i>

493
00:35:55,821 --> 00:35:58,255
WHAT?
<i>[ Broots ]</i>
<i>IT SAYS OUT HERE:</i>

494
00:35:58,324 --> 00:36:02,359
<i>"TO OPEN, PULL THE</i>
<i>'DO NOT PULL' LEVER INSIDE."</i>

495
00:36:02,427 --> 00:36:04,360
<i>REALLY!</i>

496
00:36:09,000 --> 00:36:11,334
<i> [ Buzzer Sounds ]</i>

497
00:36:13,171 --> 00:36:15,338
<i> JAROD SHIPPED US BACK</i>
<i> TO THE CENTRE?</i>

498
00:36:15,407 --> 00:36:19,509
- IRONIC, ISN'T IT?
- IT'S A REGULAR JUNIOR JUMBLE.

499
00:36:19,578 --> 00:36:21,511
WHEN I CATCH HIM,
I'M GONNA KILL HIM.

500
00:36:21,580 --> 00:36:24,914
- WELL, YOU MAY GET YOUR CHANCE.
- WE TRACKED HIM TO
AN ARMY SURVIVAL CAMP.

501
00:36:24,983 --> 00:36:27,550
- WHERE?
- IT'S IN TEXAS,

502
00:36:27,620 --> 00:36:30,253
RIGHT NEXT TO THE CONTAINER YARD
WHERE YOU STARTED.

503
00:36:38,263 --> 00:36:41,798
WELCOME BACK, LADIES.
SORRY TO RUIN YOUR "R" AND "R,"

504
00:36:41,867 --> 00:36:45,101
BUT WE HAVE NEW ORDERS TO
MOVE UP YOUR THREE-DAY SURVIVAL
SOLO INTO THE WILDERNESS.

505
00:36:45,170 --> 00:36:46,869
<i>YOU'LL BE ASSIGNED</i>
<i>SEPARATE QUADRANTS.</i>

506
00:36:46,938 --> 00:36:49,906
YOUR MISSION
IS TO ESCAPE AND EVADE
FOR THE NEXT 72 HOURS.

507
00:36:49,975 --> 00:36:51,908
ALL THAT YOU NEED
AND ALL THAT YOU ARE GETTING...

508
00:36:51,977 --> 00:36:53,910
IS IN YOUR GEAR,
WHICH YOU CAN PICK UP
AT THE TABLE.

509
00:36:53,979 --> 00:36:56,112
MAKE ME PROUD!
LET'S GO!
[ All Shouting ]

510
00:36:56,181 --> 00:36:58,281
LET'S GO!
MAKE ME PROUD!

511
00:36:58,350 --> 00:36:59,949
LET'S GO! COME ON!

512
00:37:00,019 --> 00:37:01,985
<i>[ Shouting Continues ]</i>
<i>MOVE IT!</i>

513
00:37:02,054 --> 00:37:04,154
<i>LET'S GO!</i>
<i>ALL RIGHT!</i>

514
00:37:55,674 --> 00:37:59,276
[ Yelling ]

515
00:38:02,948 --> 00:38:05,715
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>
<i>WAKE UP, SAUNDERS.</i>

516
00:38:05,784 --> 00:38:08,085
<i> WAKE UP!</i>

517
00:38:09,088 --> 00:38:12,456
WHERE AM I?
WHAT'S HAPPENING?

518
00:38:12,524 --> 00:38:16,626
I BET SCOTT RION
ASKED HIMSELF THE SAME QUESTION.

519
00:38:16,695 --> 00:38:19,963
- WHO'S IN HERE?
- JUST DEMONS IN YOUR MIND.

520
00:38:20,032 --> 00:38:22,132
<i>AND VICTIMS FROM YOUR PAST.</i>
[ Gasps ]

521
00:38:22,201 --> 00:38:25,702
<i>WHAT'S THE MATTER, SAUNDERS?</i>
<i>FEELING A LITTLE CRAZY?</i>

522
00:38:25,771 --> 00:38:28,371
- STEVENS, IS THAT YOU?
- YOU LOOK SCARED.

523
00:38:28,440 --> 00:38:30,306
<i> SCARED TO DEATH!</i>

524
00:38:30,375 --> 00:38:32,208
[ Yells ]

525
00:38:34,146 --> 00:38:38,181
THIS IS GONNA COST YOU
YOUR COMMISSION.

526
00:38:38,250 --> 00:38:40,917
WELL, IT CAN'T REALLY
COST ME MY COMMISSION, BECAUSE
I DON'T REALLY HAVE ONE.

527
00:38:40,986 --> 00:38:43,319
THE TRUTH IS,
MY NAME'S NOT STEVENS.

528
00:38:43,388 --> 00:38:46,022
I'M NOT EVEN IN THE ARMY.
[ Chuckles ]

529
00:38:46,091 --> 00:38:48,391
WHAT HAVE YOU DONE TO ME?

530
00:38:48,460 --> 00:38:50,593
THE SAME THING YOU DID
TO SCOTT RION.
[ Echoing ]

531
00:38:50,662 --> 00:38:52,796
RION HUNG HIMSELF.

532
00:38:52,864 --> 00:38:54,864
HE COULDN'T COPE.
I TOLD YOU THAT!

533
00:38:54,933 --> 00:38:57,700
<i>BECAUSE OF THE HALLUCINOGENS</i>
<i>YOU PUT IN HIS M.R.E.</i>

534
00:38:57,769 --> 00:39:01,905
DRUGS YOU DESIGNED TO INCREASE
HIS FEELINGS OF FEAR AND TERROR.

535
00:39:01,974 --> 00:39:04,607
MAN, THIS IS CRAZY!

536
00:39:04,676 --> 00:39:06,876
ALMOST AS CRAZY
AS SCOTT RION MUST HAVE FELT...

537
00:39:06,945 --> 00:39:08,878
WHEN YOU LEFT HIM
IN THE HOLE ALL NIGHT!

538
00:39:08,947 --> 00:39:12,115
<i>AS THE DRUG</i>
<i>TOOK CONTROL OF HIS MIND,</i>
<i>HE HAD TWO OPTIONS--</i>

539
00:39:12,184 --> 00:39:14,384
EITHER GO CRAZY,
OR KILL HIMSELF.

540
00:39:14,453 --> 00:39:16,118
NO! NO!

541
00:39:16,187 --> 00:39:20,223
YOU KNEW HE WAS GOING
TO REPORT YOU FOR THE SEXUAL
HARASSMENT OF LT. KIMBRALL.

542
00:39:20,292 --> 00:39:24,795
YOU WOULD HAVE BEEN
COURT-MARTIALED,
LOST YOUR PRECIOUS CAREER.

543
00:39:24,863 --> 00:39:27,764
YOU CAN'T PROVE ANY OF IT.
YOU CAN'T PROVE IT.

544
00:39:27,832 --> 00:39:32,635
THAT'S WHY I WHIPPED UP
MY OWN LITTLE SPECIAL BATCH...

545
00:39:32,704 --> 00:39:34,370
<i>OF ABYSS.</i>

546
00:39:34,439 --> 00:39:37,073
- [ Gasping ]
- AS YOU KNOW,
IT STARTS OUT SLOWLY.

547
00:39:37,142 --> 00:39:40,243
AND THEN IT BUILDS,
GETTING STRONGER
WITH EACH WAVE...

548
00:39:40,311 --> 00:39:43,279
UNTIL YOUR MIND SLOWLY
SLIPS INTO INSANITY.

549
00:39:43,348 --> 00:39:45,314
IT SHOULD BE KICKING IN
PRETTY WELL RIGHT NOW.

550
00:39:45,383 --> 00:39:48,751
YOUR EYES
PLAYIN' TRICKS ON YOU?
YOUR SKIN CRAWLING?

551
00:39:48,820 --> 00:39:51,054
YOUR MIND LOSING ITS GRIP?

552
00:39:51,122 --> 00:39:55,158
<i> OH, UH, THE KEY</i>
<i> TO YOUR HANDCUFFS.</i>

553
00:39:55,227 --> 00:39:58,762
<i>YOU SHOULD HAVE YOUR HANDS FREE</i>
<i>IN CASE YOU WANNA</i>
<i>MUTILATE YOURSELF.</i>

554
00:39:58,830 --> 00:40:03,599
<i> WELL, GOTTA GO NOW.</i>
<i> HAVE FUN IN YOUR OWN</i>
<i> PRIVATE LITTLE...</i>

555
00:40:03,668 --> 00:40:06,469
<i> HELL.</i>

556
00:40:06,538 --> 00:40:10,240
OH, ONE MORE THING.
RION'S BELT,

557
00:40:10,309 --> 00:40:13,576
<i>JUST IN CASE YOU WOULD WANT</i>
<i>TO, UH, HANG AROUND.</i>

558
00:40:15,714 --> 00:40:19,482
- HAVE FUN.
- WAIT! WAIT!
DON'T LEAVE ME IN HERE!

559
00:40:19,551 --> 00:40:21,818
<i> WAIT! DON'T LEAVE!</i>

560
00:40:21,887 --> 00:40:24,287
[ Whimpering ]

561
00:40:24,355 --> 00:40:26,522
<i> LET ME OUT, MAN!</i>

562
00:40:31,029 --> 00:40:34,497
<i> LOOK.</i>
<i> YOU'RE RIGHT!</i>

563
00:40:34,566 --> 00:40:37,567
OKAY? I DID IT!
I DID IT!

564
00:40:37,635 --> 00:40:40,203
[ Panting ]
I DRUGGED HIM.

565
00:40:40,272 --> 00:40:42,471
<i> [ Sobbing ]</i>
<i> I DRUGGED HIM.</i>

566
00:40:46,111 --> 00:40:48,278
<i> COME ON, MAN!</i>
<i> LET ME OUT!</i>

567
00:40:48,347 --> 00:40:52,315
MMM-- UH-UH.

568
00:40:52,384 --> 00:40:54,884
<i>LET ME OUT!</i>

569
00:40:54,953 --> 00:40:57,454
HOW LONG SHOULD
WE LEAVE HIM IN THERE?

570
00:40:57,523 --> 00:40:59,989
THE DRUG SHOULD WEAR OFF
IN A COUPLE OF HOURS.
AFTER THAT,

571
00:41:00,058 --> 00:41:01,991
HE'LL JUST WEEP.

572
00:41:02,060 --> 00:41:06,496
<i> [ Panting ]</i>
<i> LET ME OUT!</i>

573
00:41:21,246 --> 00:41:24,247
<i>[ Kimbrall ]</i>
<i>THE COLONEL ASSURES ME SAUNDERS</i>
<i>WILL GET EVERYTHING HE DESERVES.</i>

574
00:41:24,316 --> 00:41:27,450
TWENTY TO LIFE
AT LEAVENWORTH MINIMUM.

575
00:41:27,518 --> 00:41:30,987
AND RION'S FAMILY WILL GET
A FULL APOLOGY
AND DISCLOSURE OF WHAT HAPPENED.

576
00:41:31,056 --> 00:41:32,989
FROM COLONEL DANCE
PERSONALLY.

577
00:41:33,058 --> 00:41:35,092
THANK YOU, LIEUTENANT.
AND I HAVE A FEELING...

578
00:41:35,160 --> 00:41:37,327
THOSE BARS OF YOURS
WON'T BE LONG IN COMING.

579
00:41:37,396 --> 00:41:39,996
YOU KNOW, I DON'T KNOW
YOUR RANK, JAROD,

580
00:41:40,065 --> 00:41:42,565
BUT I AM HONORED
TO CALL YOU "SIR."

581
00:41:44,002 --> 00:41:46,335
THANK YOU.

582
00:41:49,407 --> 00:41:51,508
NOW IF YOU'LL EXCUSE ME,
I'M GOING TO PRACTICE
SOME OF THOSE...

583
00:41:51,576 --> 00:41:53,943
ESCAPE AND EVASION SKILLS
I'VE LEARNED HERE.

584
00:41:54,012 --> 00:41:56,346
GOOD LUCK.

585
00:42:03,821 --> 00:42:06,722
<i>[ Phone Ringing ]</i>

586
00:42:09,428 --> 00:42:12,028
WHAT?
[ Jarod ]
ASIDE FROM THE CHIPPED MOLAR,

587
00:42:12,096 --> 00:42:14,898
IT SOUNDS LIKE
YOU SURVIVED.
NO THANKS TO YOU.

588
00:42:14,966 --> 00:42:17,200
ACTUALLY, EVERYTHING YOU NEEDED
WAS THERE ALL ALONG.

589
00:42:17,268 --> 00:42:19,201
ALL YOU HAD TO DO
WAS OPEN YOUR EYES AND SEE.

590
00:42:20,906 --> 00:42:23,740
WHAT EXACTLY WAS IT
I WAS SUPPOSED TO SEE?

591
00:42:23,809 --> 00:42:26,275
THAT SURVIVAL COMES DOWN
TO KNOWING THE DIFFERENCE...

592
00:42:26,345 --> 00:42:29,379
BETWEEN YOUR FRIENDS
AND YOUR ENEMIES.

593
00:42:29,447 --> 00:42:31,381
I SUPPOSE YOU'RE TRYING
TO TELL ME THAT...

594
00:42:31,450 --> 00:42:33,883
LYLE IS MY ENEMY
AND YOU'RE MY FRIEND.

595
00:42:33,952 --> 00:42:36,319
MAYBE. AND YOU HAVE
TO BE WILLING...

596
00:42:36,388 --> 00:42:39,189
TO DO WHATEVER IT TAKES
TO SURVIVE.

597
00:42:39,257 --> 00:42:41,558
YOU CAN SURE BET
THAT LYLE WILL.

598
00:42:41,626 --> 00:42:43,727
[ Line Disconnects ]

599
00:42:50,601 --> 00:42:53,036
[ Gunfire ]

600
00:42:54,105 --> 00:42:56,339
[ Man Shouts ]
[ Gunfire ]

601
00:42:56,408 --> 00:42:59,075
<i>[ Man Shouts ]</i>

